ce:section.ce:para:
In this research, parameters corresponding to the engine performance such as engine power, BSFC, and emission of pollutants including NOx, HC, and soot were assessed. To perform such experiments, a single-cylinder four-stroke engine was exploited which was also connected to a dynamometer apparatus to measure the eddy current (Fig. 1
                        ). The air-cooled single-cylinder engine manufactured by Lombardini (Italy) was adopted and its features are shown in Table 4
                        . The eddy-current-mode dynamometer was used to perform the experiments which can evaluate the maximum power of 21 hp, maximum rate of 10,000 rpm, and maximum torque of 80 N m. In this device, in order to assess the torque level and rotational speed, a magnetic field was applied. Furthermore, in this system, temperature monitoring of the engine oil, exhaust gases, and surrounding environment was carried out by sensors which were placed on the engine. To monitor the parameters associated with the engine and dynamometer, a central monitoring system was employed, data of which was recorded.
